TITLE: Mexico COVID-19 infections up, especially at tourism centers
SUMMARY: COVID-19 infections are rising across Mexico, especially in two states home to major tourism destinations on the Caribbean Sea and Pacific Ocean that were busy during the holiday season

TITLE: Steps urged as 3 women slain in a day by partners in France
SUMMARY: Three women in France were found dead on New Year’s Day, allegedly killed by their partners, despite efforts by President Emmanuel Macron’s government to rein in deadly domestic violence

TITLE: Palestinian prisoner ends hunger strike in deal with Israel
SUMMARY: A Palestinian prisoner who has been on hunger strike for over 140 days to protest being imprisoned without charge will end his fast after reaching a deal with Israel to be released next month

TITLE: Lebanon's pound hits low of 30,000 to a dollar amid crisis
SUMMARY: Lebanon’s currency has hit a new low, reaching 20 times its value on the black market since the economic meltdown began in late 2019 and likely throwing more people into poverty

TITLE: South African leader gets first part of corruption report
SUMMARY: South African President Cyril Ramaphosa has received the first part of a report on corruption from a judicial investigation into allegations of graft during former President Jacob Zuma’s tenure from 2009 to 2018

TITLE: US takes custody of suspect in Haitian president slaying
SUMMARY: U.S. authorities have taken custody of a main suspect in the killing of Haitian president Jovenel Moïse

TITLE: Anti-coup protests in Sudan amid turmoil after PM resigns
SUMMARY: Sudanese have flooded the streets in the capital of Khartoum and other cities in anti-coup protests as the country plunges further into turmoil following the prime minister's resignation earlier this week

TITLE: Troubled Chinese developer told to demolish resort
SUMMARY: A troubled Chinese real estate developer that is struggling with $310 billion in debt has suffered a new blow after it was ordered to demolish a 39-building resort complex

TITLE: Sri Lanka leader sacks minister who criticized farm policy
SUMMARY: Sri Lanka's president has sacked a government minister after he criticized a now-abandoned government decision to ban chemical fertilizers

TITLE: Record number of migrant boats crossed Channel in 2021
SUMMARY: At least 28,300 people packed into small boats crossed the Channel from France to England’s south coast in 2021

TITLE: Puerto Rico battles COVID-19 surge, imposes new measures
SUMMARY: Puerto Rico is imposing new measures to fight a surge in COVID-19 cases that has overwhelmed medical staff in the U.S. territory and led to temporary shortages of testing kits

TITLE: Sweden prosecutes woman for recruiting son to fight in Syria
SUMMARY: Swedish public prosecutors say they have charged a 49-year-old woman from Sweden with war crimes for allegedly assisting in getting her son to fight in Syria as a child soldier

TITLE: Polish miners block coal for power plants to demand pay hike
SUMMARY: Miners employed by Poland's largest coal company are blocking deliveries of the fossil fuel to power plants to demand higher pay to keep pace with surging consumer prices

TITLE: Italy sets Jan 24 to start voting for new president
SUMMARY: Italy has set Jan. 24 as the start date to begin voting for a new Italian president

TITLE: NATO to hold foreign ministers meeting over Ukraine
SUMMARY: The NATO alliance will hold a virtual meeting of foreign ministers from the 30 member nations on Friday to assess the situation in Ukraine and upcoming talks with Russia

TITLE: Suspects held after fake online sale of Indian Muslim women
SUMMARY: Police in India have detained a man and a woman alleged to be involved in the offering for sale of prominent Muslim women on a fake online auction website in a case that has sparked outrage across the country

TITLE: Sri Lanka to sign oil terminal deal with India
SUMMARY: Sri Lanka has agreed with India to jointly develop a strategic oil terminal consisting of nearly 100 large oil tanks

TITLE: Suspected militant accused of beheadings killed in Indonesia
SUMMARY: Indonesian security forces have killed a suspected militant accused of beheadings in a shootout Tuesday in a sweeping counterterrorism campaign against extremists in remote mountain jungles

TITLE: Zimbabwe journalists mourn passing of editor Iden Wetherell
SUMMARY: Zimbabwean journalists are praising Iden Wetherell, one of the country’s most principled and exacting editors, who died on Dec. 23 after a battle with Alzheimer’s

TITLE: Suspect in South Africa's Parliament fire appears in court
SUMMARY: The man suspected of starting the fire that gutted South Africa’s parliament buildings has appeared in court and will remain in custody pending his application for bail

TITLE: Albanian wanted over police killing arrested in Germany
SUMMARY: German police say an Albanian man who disappeared after serving part of a sentence for his role in the killing of a high-ranking police officer in his homeland two decades ago has been arrested at Frankfurt Airport

TITLE: Hong Kong's Lam: Media closures unrelated to press freedom
SUMMARY: Hong Kong leader Carrie Lam says the recent closure of two media outlets in the city does not indicate a decline in press freedom as the decisions were made by the outlets themselves

TITLE: US-led coalition: Attack with 2 armed drones foiled in Iraq
SUMMARY: A U.S.-led coalition official in Iraq says two explosives-laden drones that targeted a military base housing U.S. troops in western Anbar province have been destroyed

TITLE: Germany's Steinmeier on course for 2nd term as president
SUMMARY: Germany’s environmentalist Greens have come out in favor of a second term for President Frank-Walter Steinmeier

TITLE: Landslide in southwestern China kills 14 people, injures 3
SUMMARY: A landslide at a construction site in southwestern China has killed 14 people and injured three others
